lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money</span><hr size=1> Depends on their situation, Therus...  If they're already in tell hell from guildies or the like, it's a huge pain.  If they're in the middle of a fight with several adds, it's just more spam that flies by on their screen that may make them miss a &quot;xxx is mezed&quot; or &quot;HEAL!&quot; message.  If they're afk, they'll never see it.  It also means they have to do a /who all on you, just to make sure you're not asking for a port to DL from Steamfont, when you're in the Bazaar or something.  You just never know what type of situation they're in.  Then there's the fact that the porter is *expected* to reply, otherwise the person making the request assumes that you missed it, and you get another tell every 30 seconds until you do reply (I once went afk for an hour, apparently just as someone started asking for a port...  Counted 37 tells from that one person when I got back).  :/  Goes back to the &quot;never expect something of a porter&quot; deal.  In my 52 levels as a druid, I've always been far more likely to give people ports if they just /ooc it than if they send me a tell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uronaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 4:36:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21993.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Money</span><hr size=1> My &quot;get a port&quot; rules that I try to follow whenever I can:<br>
<br>
- offer money. usually 50 pp will do it. I prefer translocates over groupgates because it saves the porter time as well. I might go LD on zoning and groupbug them... translocates are much nicer.<br>
<br>
- I usually send a tell to someone sitting around and doing nothing, being polite and typing in full sentences and words (hate plz myself).<br>
<br>
- not much a monk can offer to compensate the mana loss, on my necro I offer a twitch or 3 to go with the money<br>
<br>
- if no wizards or druids are on /who, I'll auction 50 pp for port / TL to whathaveyou (bound in shadowhaven so I'm not out of the world really, TL bind will almost always do the thing)<br>
<br>
